&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;??&lt;/code&gt; checks If something is &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;null&lt;/code&gt;. If it’s not null it returns it’s own value but if it’s &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;null&lt;/code&gt; it returns the value after &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;??&lt;/code&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;return abc??10;     //reutrns 10 if abc is null else returns it&amp;#39;s own value,&lt;/code&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It also has shorthand assignment when it’s null.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;abc??=5     //assigns 5 to abc if it&amp;#39;s null&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
